# canGoForward

**Instance Property**

A Boolean value indicating whether the receiver can move forward.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor var canGoForward: Bool { get }
```

## Discussion

If [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true], able to move forward; otherwise, [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false] .

## Moving back and forward

- **canGoBack**: A Boolean value indicating whether the receiver can move backward.
- **goBack()**: Loads the previous location in the back-forward list.
- **goForward()**: Loads the next location in the back-forward list.
